                        <h1>Global Media Awards</h1>                                  
                        <IMG height=138 src="/print/images/content/GlobalMediaAwardsCombo275.gif" width=275 align=right>The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) and the National Academy of Television Arts and Sciences (NATAS) are partnering to launch a new <A href="http://www.globalmediaawards.org/" target=_blank>Global Media Awards program</A> focused on technology and content programming at the 2009 CES. <BR><BR>Peter O. Price, President and CEO of NATAS, applauded the joint initiative, noting, "We anticipate wide participation and attendance at the ceremony, which will invite entries from a broad spectrum of creators, producers, and distributors of content and technologies."<BR><BR>
<TABLE style="BORDER-RIGHT: #9f9f9f 1px solid; BORDER-TOP: #9f9f9f 1px solid; BORDER-LEFT: #9f9f9f 1px solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #9f9f9f 1px solid" cellPadding=8>
<TBODY>
