<TD>
<H3>Discounted tickets available for CES attendees</H3>
<P>Join us for the inaugural banquet ceremony of the Global Media Awards at The Venetian Hotel on the opening night of CES, January 8, 2009,&nbsp;launching with a special recognition of the chief executives of the leading mobile telephone manufacturers who have pioneered the future of digital communications and competitive digital content awards whose nominees include the leading creative networks, channels and agencies of CBS, NBC, FOX, BBC, Warner Brothers, You Tube, Sundance, Discovery, DIRECTV, BBDO, McCann Erikson, Bravo, MTV, Disney, The New York Times, Starz, Wieden + Kennedy, Ogilvy, ESPN, Sony, Turner, NASCAR, HSN and Scripps.<BR><BR>Networking cocktail reception at 6 p.m. with dinner and presentation at 7 p.m. There is a special rate of $400 for CES attendees. E-mail <A href="mailto:events@natasonline.com">events@natasonline.com</A> or call 212-484-9440 with any questions and to take advantage of the discount.</P></TD></TR></TBODY></TABLE><BR>Categories for the Global Media Awards include short form, advertising, website/Internet, repurposed linear/traditional content, long form, platform and user experience/program guide. <A href="http://www.emmyonline.org/mediacenter/global_0708_nominees.html" target=_blank>View the list of nominees.</A><BR><BR>For information about the Global Media Awards, <A href="mailto:ppillitteri@natasonline.com">e-mail Paul Pillitteri</A> or visit <A href="http://www.globalmediaawards.org/" target=_blank>GlobalMediaAwards.org</A>.
    
